reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love it, does just what it advertises
reviews.reviewText: Range of light is great, from dim and cozy to nice and bright if you need to read under it. Love that you can also set the color temperature. The 2-point swivel allows you to adjust it to many different angles. The touch features work very well. Great product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars so cute, and bright
reviews.reviewText: just turned it on for the first time and I have to leave a review! it didn’t come with instructions which it is pretty self explanatory but i was so bummed because it says dimmable and different brightness levels and there was no button to change the brightness. if you keep scrolling to the bottom though the pic shows the brightness part you literally just swipe to the brightness you need this is literally perfect. i kinda didn’t want to spend more for the pink one because i wasn’t sure if it would be bright enough tbh but i’m glad i did because it’s cute and works great. i’ll update if something bad happens lol. i’m using this so i can see my hands better when i do my nails, the first pic is with my vanity light on and this overhead light on, and the second pic is this overhead light on by itself. really helps! also don’t judge my nails i was waiting for this light to finally do them lmao

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I needed a light I could fold away when not in use
reviews.reviewText: I sometimes work at my computer desk and I have a sliding keyboard tray. It is dark if I try to work on something on the keyboard tray. I can fold the light and put it behind my keyboard when needed I move my keyboard and use the light.I have it plugged into my USB hub attached to my computer. I'm using it as a light source only. I'm not worried about a power source for charging my phone.I have no complaints, the lamp is easy to use and the folding arm comes in handy when I need to have the light source a little further on my keyboard tray. Inexpensive and gives off good light. I tend to use the white light not the yellow light. I work on models and the white light is good.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great Little Lamp for the Price
reviews.reviewText: This small lamp fits perfectly on the far corner of my worktable. Very sleek, stylish, and sturdy but it doesn't take up visual space. All parts of it are out of the way. The on-off apparatus is touch-and-glide and very easy to use. The light range is really good, ranging from a dim low to what I'd think is nearly daylight bright (and I'm in Florida). I only wish the light was a bit warmer. I find that cold light makes working with colors tricky. Fortunately, there's a window nearby.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It works perfectly for me. I don't know about you
reviews.reviewText: It fits and works perfectly for me on my small desk in the corner of my house. Other people in the house don't think it is bright enough, but I'm the one working at my desk. I was surprised by the plug being a USB plug and not the normal outlet, but it plugs into my power strip with no problem. I Like the brightness adjustment, but I haven't figured out why you would want to set a timer. Better to have and not need than to need and not have, I guess.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Awesome lamp that takes up little space but can put out some light. Easy to find on button in dark by just sliding a finger in the corner. Can switch from low light to high with ease. Love the touch controls and how it folds up nice and neat.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Glitchy USB-C connection
reviews.reviewText: The good: I really love the warm to cool and dimmable functions, and the lamp doesn't take up much space on the nightstand. I use it for very gentle warm lighting on migraine days and to color-correct the glare from outside when it's foggy, and it works well for both purposes.The bad: the USB-C port is glitchy as all hell. It started flickering if the cord wasn't *precisely* in the right position a couple months ago, and by now it flickers nearly all the time whether or not anything is even touching the cord. I'm careful to keep cords from tugging on ports as a general rule, but this will start flickering when it's been on for two hours with literally nothing else moving on the desk, or when it's turned on after having been off for two minutes, even if I tape the cord down so it can't move.Maybe mine is just glitchy, but I'm reluctant to buy a second one when the first started having trouble after 3-4 months of very careful use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars I Loved this lamp.
reviews.reviewText: I use this lamp daily in my Art Space. The light is perfect to paint by. However, I purchased this in June 2021 and today it died. Not sure what to do. Tried many different plugs and cords to see if that is the problem. Nothing worked, just dead. I may just get another one because the lighting was just so perfect for what I need. Sadness.
Does not come with a wall adapter and I don't have one at home. So I now need another piece to make this work..
